## Load data from Week 1
bikeshare <- read.csv("train.csv", header = T, sep = ",")

## Factorize holiday, workingday, season, weather
bikeshare$season <- as.factor(bikeshare$season)
bikeshare$holiday <- as.factor(bikeshare$holiday)
bikeshare$workingday <- as.factor(bikeshare$workingday)
bikeshare$weather <- as.factor(bikeshare$weather)

## convert "datetime" column datatype to posxict
bikeshare$datetime <-as.POSIXct(bikeshare$datetime,tz="","%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")

## attach the bikeshare to easily access its variables
attach(bikeshare)
library("plyr")

## Jan 2011 Data
start <- as.POSIXct('2011-01-01 00:00:00', tz="EST")
end <- as.POSIXct('2011-01-19 23:00:00', tz="EST")
time = data.frame(seq.POSIXt(from=start, to=end , by="1 hour"))
colnames(time)= c("datetime")
evenlyspacedData <- join(time, bikeshare, by = "datetime", type="left")
dataselected_jan2011 <- evenlyspacedData[,c(1,12)]

## This is forecast 7.3
dataselected_jan2011$count <- na.interp(dataselected_jan2011$count)
dataselected_mar2011$count <- na.interp(dataselected_mar2011$count)
dataselected_may2011$count <- na.interp(dataselected_may2011$count)
dataselected_aug2011$count <- na.interp(dataselected_aug2011$count)
dataselected_oct2011$count <- na.interp(dataselected_oct2011$count)
dataselected_dec2011$count <- na.interp(dataselected_dec2011$count)


############################## Fit exponential smoothing model #################################

## From the decision tree, HoltsWinter method will be used since this has trend and seasonality

## Jan 2011
jan2011TimeSeries<-ts(dataselected_jan2011$count,frequency=24)
HWModel_jan2011<-HoltWinters(jan2011TimeSeries)
plot(HWModel_jan2011, main="Jan 2011 Data with Holt Winters Model", ylim=c(-50,400), xlab="Day of the month")
text(2,400,labels=bquote(alpha == .(HWModel_jan2011$alpha)), cex=1.5, pos=4) #write alpha on the graph
text(2,350,labels=bquote(beta == .(HWModel_jan2011$beta)), cex=1.5, pos=4) #write alpha on the graph
text(2,300,labels=bquote(gamma == .(HWModel_jan2011$gamma)), cex=1.5, pos=4) #write alpha on the graph
legend("topright", c("Actual","Fitted"), lty=c(1,1), lwd = c(2,2),col = c("black","red"))

trainingset_jan2011<- ts(dataselected_jan2011$count[1:336],frequency=24)
testingset_jan2011 <- ts(dataselected_jan2011$count[337:456],frequency=24, start=c(15,1))
HWModel_train_jan2011<-HoltWinters(trainingset_jan2011)
jan2011.pred <- predict(HWModel_train_jan2011, n.ahead = 120, prediction.interval = TRUE)
MAPE1<- mean(abs(jan2011.pred[,1]-testingset_jan2011)/testingset_jan2011)*100
plot.ts(testingset_jan2011, xlim=c(15,20), ylim=c(-100,1000), xlab="Day of the month", col="green", main="Jan 2011 Forecast")
lines(jan2011.pred[,1], col="blue")
lines(jan2011.pred[,2], col="red")
lines(jan2011.pred[,3], col="red")
text(15,350,labels=paste("MAPE=",round(MAPE1,2),"%"), pos=4)
text(15,900,labels=bquote(alpha == .(HWModel_train_jan2011$alpha)), cex=1.5, pos=4) #write alpha on the graph
text(15,800,labels=bquote(beta == .(HWModel_train_jan2011$beta)), cex=1.5, pos=4) #write alpha on the graph
text(15,700,labels=bquote(gamma == .(HWModel_train_jan2011$gamma)), cex=1.5, pos=4) #write alpha on the graph
legend("topright", c("Actual","Predicted","Intervals"), lty=c(1,1), lwd = c(2,2),col = c("green","blue","red"))

## Mar 2011

## Observations:
## Of all the three models above, the predicted values follow the smoothed workingday values. Thus causing high MAPE due to incorrect forecast on non-workingdays
## Possible solution: to create two models, one for workingday and another for other days.
## The trends are very minimal in the above models 
## All models rely heavliy on Seasonal component
## Except Jan 2011 other two models rely on Level component. 




####################### Identify MA(q)/ AR(p) Process ################################


## De Trended data acf and pacf plot

## Jan 2011 
detrended_jan2011 <- diff(dataselected_jan2011$count)
deseasoned_jan2011 <- diff(dataselected_jan2011$count, lag=168)
detrend_deseasoned_jan2011 <- diff(detrended_jan2011, lag=168)

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
acf(detrended_jan2011, lag.max = 100, col="blue", main="ACF - Jan 2011 De-trended")
pacf(detrended_jan2011, lag.max = 100, col="blue", main="PACF - Jan 2011 De-trended")

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
acf(deseasoned_jan2011, lag.max = 100, col="blue", main="ACF - Jan 2011 Deseasoned")
pacf(deseasoned_jan2011, lag.max = 100, col="blue", main="PACF - Jan 2011 Deseasoned")

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
acf(detrend_deseasoned_jan2011, lag.max = 100, col="blue", main="ACF - Jan 2011 De-Trended/Deseasoned")
pacf(detrend_deseasoned_jan2011, lag.max = 100, col="blue", main="PACF - Jan 2011 De-Trended/Deseasoned")

## March 2011 Data
detrended_mar2011 <- diff(dataselected_mar2011$count)
deseasoned_mar2011 <- diff(dataselected_mar2011$count, lag=168)

par(mfrow=c(1,2))

par(mfrow=c(1,2))

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
acf(detrend_deseasoned_mar2011, lag.max = 100, col="blue", main="ACF Mar 2011 De-Trended/Deseasoned")
